decision_conditions:
Condition 3 of planning permission P2013/2733/FUL should read:

MATERIALS: Details of facing materials including samples shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to  the relevant part of the works commencing on site. The samples shall include but not be limited to details of:

a) the glazed facades including information on solar glare and obscured glazing;
b) the glazed atrium;
c) brickwork (sample panel in situ);
d) fenestration and openings;
e) the precast louvred fins;
f) the replacement roof and windows for Goswell Place and Myddelton Building; and
g) any other details or materials to be used on the exterior of the development.  

The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details and samples so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter. 

REASON: In the interests of securing sustainable development and to ensure that the resulting appearance and construction of the development is of a high standard in accordance with policies: 5.3; 7.4; 7.5 and 7.6 of the London Plan 2011, Policies CS7, CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011 and Development Management Policy DM2.1.
